codex
The timeout dump shows the remote server’s task processor is spending the whole timeout copying an ever-growing artifact history, while the producer blocks writing more artifacts. The minimal behavioral fix is to avoid forwarding unbounded in-progress remote artifact chunks as ADK events; keep aggregating them and emit the aggregate when a last chunk or final status arrives.
